That Alexandra from Yorktown Heights was a little american girl who grew up in an american town speaking america english and going through the public school system. Who later was kingmakered into this politician we see now, and felt like an imposter so she created AOC

Her wikipedia says she was born in bronx and then grew up in yorktown.  That doesn't mean your from bronx.  If you were born in texas on a military base for example, and then immediately moved and lived the rest of your life in say Kansas, is it right to claim you're from Texas well into your 20s?  No.  It's stupid and it's VIRTUAL SIGNALLING, because Texas would be 'cooler' to be from than just some rando super uncool corn hole in Kansas. (is what a sandy would think)

Being from the Bronx makes you sound tough.  Hey I'm Sandy, ya'll, from the BRONX.  She's stealing valor, actually, from those people who DO live in the bronx.  And have to fight off gangs and crime she doesn't have in peaceful and less populous Yorktown Heights.

Identifying as "a Puerto Rican girl" is another virtue signal.  It says "I'm part of a hispanic victim group that is always drawing the short straw....poor me".   This is another stolen valor.  Stealing from the POOR in this case, and trying to claim that her "Struggle" is the same as a puerto ricans.  

No it's not.  You're just some dumb fucking middle class hispanic chick, AOC, who grew up in public school.  Eveyone in a US public school system..we all grew up with some latina girl in our class (and black, and native american and.....name a group).  You are completely unspecial!  

In the biggest inversion of purpose I've seen in my lifetime......In order to be a leftist these days, one has to REJECT the previous leftist idea of the US being a melting pot of cultures.  You have to REJECT the idea that the hispanic or black girl next to you in public school class is the same as you.  That if she's making the same grades, she's the same.  If she likes the same tv shows or movies then she's the same.  Or that she has the same opportunities as you (you = what?  you = anything...hispanic, black, asian, white...all AMericans!).  You have to REJECT the idea that regardless of someone's sex, race, looks, that if they make the same grades and are naturally born american that there is nothing standing in their way to a future they will create.

All of that is wrong now.  Now, as a leftist, you have to identify with groups and encourage identitarian victimhood tribalism.  "As a latina" is a common phrase.  "As a woman"...."As a BIPOC"  etc.   and then the next thing is some permutation of "my inclusion in this victim group makes me vulnerable to".....and then finally "...which is exploited by the opposition political party"

***The left now completely owns societal dissonance thru their insistence on virtual signalling of false victimhood***

This "new modality" of societal dissonance is why AOC cannot possibly just be a normal latina girl next door that you know from school.  Because that girl is equal and has equal opportunity, and doesn't have a "Life Defining Struggle"

So she made one up.  Not just for political convenience, but it's what the left does now to signal inclusion in their trible.

She's "Sandy from the Bronx, a poor, disadvantaged Puerto Rican beauty, who has been picked on for being latina all her life and had to fight SO hard for everything she has, including being a representative in Congress..."

Because the idea that some group with unfathomable money went around vetting people who were attractive and capable of public speaking, and chose HER and turned HER into the AOC we see now, made AOC feel guilty

GUILTY

Because unearned.  After all, like I said, she was just a normal, a muggle of a person plucked from the EQUAL AND FAIR melting pot of America.  Why her?!   "Why am I getting selected out of all the people who are also equally capable and also somewaht nothing special??"

The guilt of being an imposter was too much for her.  One way to make oneself not feel like an imposter is to create the persona of the imposter and then go all in on it.  Fake it till you make it.  That's what she did.
